The paper deals with game theory and its implementation in the real world, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The mention of preventing information leakage in security protocols suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The use of clocks and time passing suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The technical depth of the paper and the use of algorithms suggest that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with necessary and sufficient conditions, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category.
